    ```javascript
function maxFrequency(nums, k) {
    nums.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let max_freq = 1, n = nums.length;
    let sum = 0;
    for (let i = 0, j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
        sum += nums[j];
        while (sum < nums[j] * (j - i + 1) - k) {
            sum -= nums[i++];
        }
        max_freq = Math.max(max_freq, j - i + 1);
    }
    return max_freq;
}
```

    1. Sort the input array, nums, in non-decreasing order.
2. Traverse the sorted array using two pointers, i and j. Initialize sum and max_freq to 0 and 1, respectively.
3. In each step, increment the sum by the element at index j (nums[j]).
4. Use a while loop to check if the current sum is less than the required sum to make all elements in the current range equal to nums[j]. If this is the case, decrement the sum by the element at index i (nums[i]) and move the index i one step forward.
5. Update the max_freq by comparing it with the current range length (j - i + 1), and pick the maximum value.
6. Continue iterating until the end of the array and return the max_freq.

